

# instructions

* the tech stack we use is nix, uv, Python 3, polars, elevenai API, openai API
* Always prioritise that tech stack over alternatives.
* this is a monorepo: perfin/ and expenses/ are independent uv projects, each with its own pyproject.toml and .venv; shell.nix at the root is shared
* type check the code after each modification, by running $ nix-shell ../shell.nix --run "ty check" from within the project directory you modified
* lint the code after each modification, by running $ nix-shell ../shell.nix --run "ruff format ." from within the project directory you modified
* avoid comments that simply state what the code is doing
* Keep the codebase as small as possible to achieve the desired features
* Avoid boilerplate code and too many abstractions
* Keep code easy to reason about

